  "prompt": "Is drinking a compulsion in the Indian Army? What if one chooses not to drink?",
  "response": "Drinking is not a compulsion in the Indian Army or in any other military organization. While alcohol is often available and social drinking may be a part of certain traditions or social gatherings within the military, it is not mandatory for personnel to partake in drinking. \n\nIndividuals who choose not to drink are fully entitled to abstain without any obligation or pressure. Leaders and peers in the Indian Army are generally respectful of personal choices regarding alcohol consumption. Additionally, military policies often emphasize responsible behavior, mental well-being, and health, encouraging a respectful and inclusive environment for all servicemen and women, regardless of their personal choices concerning alcohol.",
